channel.title: I need help removing a slight error
channel.description:
I had this working perfectly and i fixed this problem at one point but now it decided to be ghey and error out, im pretty sure i didn't have the groovy files before but now its demanding them.
also the dynamic region error a monkey could figure out but im a idiot.... someone help.
edit: groovy error was easy :palm: im still getting the region errors.
Edit: i am using netbeans since all of my friends have been pushing me to use it, i set the source up in the Ide and compiled it just to check if anything was missing and after entering the missing symbols it says there not supposed to be there. i really want to learn java overall and im really determined.
Id like to fix this source so i can add small things and play with a couple friends :o also if you know how to remove the Christmas event and switch it back to normal i would be in your debt forever.
Edit: 8:05pm, i don't know if this is what you mean but here you go. i am using arios 498# btw, sorry i didn't tell you that sooner. Region.load(DynamicRegion.super); is still there.
@sk8r I don't know which file....
http://pastebin.com/N6WGCjGk
http://pastebin.com/uAmntrPK
http://pastebin.com/A4aBd7js
I'm sorry i am making you guys go on a wild goose chase.... :o I just don't know what file you want but i hope its in one of those.... i think the method is in DynamicRegion.java
